lead_paragraph: The Chicago Cubs' dramatic ending of a 108-year World Series drought was not merely a case of baseball's "Loveable Losers" finally catching a break but the result of a patient strategy five years in the making.

headline.print_headline: Five Years in the Making,' The Plan' Ends Cubs Drought
